{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legislate to protect rights of self-employed security personnel to fair payment",
        "additional_details": "We want this law to:\r\n- Establish statutory protections and rights to secure payment and enable action in defence of life;\r\n- Investigate possibly coercive practices within the private security industry;\r\n- Create a public registry or ombudsman to oversee complaints and uphold professional standards in the sector.\r\n",
        "background": "We urge the Government to pass a law which protects self-employed individuals in the security sector from exploitation by larger firms who may withhold payments unfairly, possibly knowing self-employed individuals lack the legal and financial means to pursue lengthy court proceedings.",
